whose leaders have been building foreign policy in a pragmatic, multivector fashion are increasingly vying for a role in ending Russia's war against Ukraine.\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6341597144939926, \"rank\": 0.5768898230911534, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commons\", \"score\": 0.9999999995566213, \"rank\": 4.4351646746145774e-10, \"text\": \"Wikimedia Commons\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commons\"}, {\"begin\": 417, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 438, \"end\": 445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These missions, some of them more self-serving than others, compete with Volodymyr Zelensky's peace plan, which Ukraine keeps trying to defend in its interactions with foreign powers.In recent months, a willingness to mediate between the warring nations has been expressed by Hungary's prime minister Viktor Orb\\u00e1n, India's prime minister Narendra Modi, Bulgarian prime minister Dimitar Glavchev, Turkish foreign minister Hakan Fidan, and China's and Brazil's top foreign policy officials.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Volodymyr Zelensky\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999583452730956, \"rank\": 2.7209414879838112e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 748, \"end\": 760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"score\": 0.9999999890105756, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viktor Orb\\u00e1n\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\"}, {\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.7357159913827827, \"rank\": 0.2873268478506585, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Narendra Modi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Bulgaria\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bulgarian prime minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Bulgaria\"}, {\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\", \"score\": 0.723270439920007, \"rank\": 0.3826086956520989, \"text\": \"Turkish foreign minister\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\"}, {\"begin\": 868, \"end\": 879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Fidan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hakan Fidan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Fidan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Fidan\"}, {\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999997288100898, \"rank\": 2.563446331994026e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 897, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9909979642430926, \"rank\": 0.00908352581463502, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Saudi Arabia, which has a decent working relationship with Russia, maybe interested too, some expertshave suggested.\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.377185077373162e-12, \"text\": \"Arabia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0Ukraine-organized summit held in June in Switzerland was intended to make sure as many countries as possible stood behind the Ukrainian peace formula, or at least the most crucial parts of it.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999969584042319, \"rank\": 3.0412770005231652e-06, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999552801465, \"rank\": 4.463501037987736e-08, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thejoint communiqu\\u00e9ended up containing just the kinds of issues the Swiss side deemed least divisive.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999683683877945, \"rank\": 2.9893672242288955e-05, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those were the safety of Ukraine's nuclear installations, a call not to use nuclear weapons, global food security, a full prisoner exchange, and the return of the deported children.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1378, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A debate over Russia's reparations to Ukraine or Moscow's responsibility for war crimes would narrow the list of the signatories.\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1573, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 1584, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999998976818, \"rank\": 1.0231740133773154e-10, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even this \\\"safe\\\" version was signed by 83 country representatives out of more than 100 participants.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazil, India, Indonesia, South Africa, Saudi Arabia, and Indiadid not signthe communiqu\\u00e9, and China did not participate in the meeting altogether.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1769, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9909979642430926, \"rank\": 0.00908352581463502, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.7357159913827827, \"rank\": 0.2873268478506585, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9998249895427296, \"rank\": 0.00017504109114482844, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999299689, \"rank\": 7.011748782069542e-11, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.377185077373162e-12, \"text\": \"Arabia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}, {\"begin\": 1864, \"end\": 1869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999997288100898, \"rank\": 2.563446331994026e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians from the global south are not inclined to support Ukraine's-and the West's-approach to peace that involves punishing Russia.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2046, \"end\": 2052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who did not sign are among the new prospective peacemakers.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Interestingly, Hungary and Turkey who are making a point of talking to both sides in the war, did sign the communiqu\\u00e9.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2138, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999583452730956, \"rank\": 2.7209414879838112e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999999957321961, \"rank\": 4.267712606838481e-09, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where Potential Peacemakers Stand  Viktor Orb\\u00e1n's push for negotiations aligns with his broader strategy to shift the European focus from military support for Ukraine to peace negotiations, experts from the Institute for the Study of Warsuggest.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2280, \"end\": 2292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"score\": 0.9999999890105756, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viktor Orb\\u00e1n\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\"}, {\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Hungary assumed the EU Council presidency on July 1, Orb\\u00e1n has consistently opposed the EU's military assistance to Ukraine, emphasizing instead the need for a diplomatic resolution.\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999583452730956, \"rank\": 2.7209414879838112e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_the_Council_of_the_European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"EU Council presidency\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_the_Council_of_the_European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_the_Council_of_the_European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2547, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"score\": 0.9988649868609479, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Orb\\u00e1n\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Orb\\u00e1n\"}, {\"begin\": 2582, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.502465854714984e-14, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2610, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This Russia-supported stance aims to dilute the EU's unified support for Ukraine.Orb\\u00e1n is also building a foreign policy toward China that is independent of the EU's policy of reducing dependence on China as a major exporter to Europe.Orb\\u00e1n and his government officials insist that Hungary should attract more Chinese investment to reduce dependence on Western capital markets,notes Re:Russia, a Russian expert platform.Turkey, another player that is eager to maintain relations with both the West and Russia, has also been suggesting itself as a mediator.\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.502465854714984e-14, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999997288100898, \"rank\": 2.563446331994026e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2838, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.502465854714984e-14, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999997288100898, \"rank\": 2.563446331994026e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999583452730956, \"rank\": 2.7209414879838112e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 2987, \"end\": 2994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999948757235285, \"rank\": 4.9457550928156405e-06, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3073, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.8273323630652956, \"rank\": 0.20862522461043606, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 3179, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Turkish foreign minister Hakan Fidanproposedestablishing a peace platform to prevent deepening polarization and prioritize diplomacy.\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3234, \"end\": 3258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\", \"score\": 0.723270439920007, \"rank\": 0.3826086956520989, \"text\": \"Turkish foreign minister\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Turkey)\"}, {\"begin\": 3259, \"end\": 3264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Yakin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5118990607190356e-19, \"text\": \"Hakan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Yakin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hakan_Yakin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Turkey has done some successful mediating before.\", \"from\": 3368, \"to\": 3417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3368, \"end\": 3374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999999957321961, \"rank\": 4.267712606838481e-09, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was instrumental inreopeningthe Black Sea to grain shipments from Ukraine.Saudi Arabia is seen as one of the potential hosts of the next peace summit that would follow up on the work done at the June summit.\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3501, \"end\": 3507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.377185077373162e-12, \"text\": \"Arabia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That potential summit, most participants agreed, would include Russia's representatives.\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3692, \"end\": 3698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Saudi strategy focuses on maintaining strategic autonomy and engaging with all major global players to enhance its diplomatic influence.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3722, \"end\": 3727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"score\": 0.999434550709166, \"rank\": 0.0005657654650196198, \"text\": \"Saudi\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saudi_Arabia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United Arab Emirates may also join an alternative peacemaking mission.\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 3934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3864, \"end\": 3884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.4802885338798032e-11, \"text\": \"United Arab Emirates\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UAE has alreadyfacilitatedbehind-the-scenes negotiations on a prisoner exchange between Ukraine and Russia.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3939, \"end\": 3942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\", \"score\": 0.9999999999668034, \"rank\": 3.334380078516477e-11, \"text\": \"UAE\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Arab_Emirates\"}, {\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 4039, \"end\": 4045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazil and China have also joined forces to advocate for peace talks, emphasizing the need for negotiation as the only viable solution to the conflict.\", \"from\": 4048, \"to\": 4199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4048, \"end\": 4054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9909979642430926, \"rank\": 0.00908352581463502, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Empire_of_Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 4059, \"end\": 4064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999997288100898, \"rank\": 2.563446331994026e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Theirjoint statementcalls for Russia and Ukraine to adhere to three principles: no expansion of the battlefield, no escalation of fighting, and no provocation.\", \"from\": 4200, \"to\": 4359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4230, \"end\": 4236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4241, \"end\": 4248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both nations stress the importance of preventing the use of weapons of mass destruction and promoting nuclear nonproliferation.\", \"from\": 4360, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Clash of Value Statements Hinders Ending the Conflict  At peace summits and in broader communications with the world, Ukraine speaks the language of values.\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4611, \"end\": 4618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It rightly condemns unprovoked aggression by authoritarian Russia against a country seeking self-determination based on a conscious democratic choice.\", \"from\": 4650, \"to\": 4800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4709, \"end\": 4715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Western politicians and intellectuals have alsoused the language of values, arguing that by supporting Ukraine, they are supporting the right to democratic self-determination in the face of authoritarian aggression.\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 5016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4904, \"end\": 4911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4478620498569474e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kremlin is insisting on a \\\"morality\\\" of its own.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5022, \"end\": 5029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9736705105624864, \"rank\": 0.02402096336881434, \"text\": \"Kremlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It claims to be waging a \\\"liberation struggle\\\" against Ukrainian \\\"Nazism\\\" and the imposed U.S.-dominated world order that disqualifies Russia.\", \"from\": 5071, \"to\": 5213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5126, \"end\": 5135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999552801465, \"rank\": 4.463501037987736e-08, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing is wrong with moral statements as such, particularly when they are honest.\", \"from\": 5215, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But moral stance may be a problem at negotiations.\", \"from\": 5298, \"to\": 5348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In hisbookAmerican Diplomacy,George Kennan argued that American politicians' tendency to frame every conflict in moral terms was not helpful in building a pragmatic foreign policy.\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5378, \"end\": 5391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.851339120802407e-64, \"text\": \"George Kennan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_F._Kennan\"}, {\"begin\": 5404, \"end\": 5412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.325705564411834e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Walt, professor of international affairs at Harvard, who reminds his readers about Kennan's view, writes that moral or value-based language can be useful for rallying citizens and winning support.\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5531, \"end\": 5543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Walt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Walt\"}, {\"begin\": 5583, \"end\": 5590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 0.999999999609372, \"rank\": 3.8955304975600866e-10, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it makes it harder for U.S. officials to bargain effectively with potential adversaries, either because we refuse to have diplomatic relations with them, or because even a mutually beneficial deal with a supposedly 'evil' regime is seen as a cowardly failure to uphold key moral principles,\\\" Waltwrites.\", \"from\": 5736, \"to\": 6044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Bargaining Might Succeed    When the United States is not seen as an effective mediator, other powers are eager to try their hand.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6089, \"end\": 6102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6341597144939926, \"rank\": 0.5768898230911534, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians who are not inclined to value-based approaches to settlements and who do not demonstrate a willingness to take sides and join the West or Russia eventually enter the peacebuilding arena.\", \"from\": 6183, \"to\": 6381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6333, \"end\": 6339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A majority of countries tend to adopt positions of multi-alignment, of double-dealing between Western countries and the emerging or re-emerging powers of the South in the broad sense of the term, including Russia,\\\"saysJean-Joseph Boillot, associate research fellow at IRIS.\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6480, \"end\": 6487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999999886313, \"rank\": 1.0398824817237468e-11, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}, {\"begin\": 6592, \"end\": 6598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 6654, \"end\": 6658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IRIS_Consortium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.0165121293479207e-12, \"text\": \"IRIS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IRIS_Consortium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IRIS_Consortium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seems increasingly likely that the fate of the war will be determined with the participation of players inclined to see it not as a conflict of values but as a conflict of interests that can be resolved through bargaining, experts from Re:Russia conclude.\", \"from\": 6663, \"to\": 6921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6905, \"end\": 6911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998394742, \"rank\": 1.601522970040766e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opinions expressed in this article are those solely of the author and do not reflect the views of the Kennan Institute.\", \"from\": 6923, \"to\": 7046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7029, \"end\": 7045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kennan Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After more than 50 years as a vital part of the Wilson Center legacy, the Kennan Institute has become an independent think tank.\", \"from\": 7048, \"to\": 7176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7096, \"end\": 7109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilson Center\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\"}, {\"begin\": 7122, \"end\": 7138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kennan Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can find the current website for the Kennan Institute at kennaninstitute.org.\", \"from\": 7177, \"to\": 7258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7218, \"end\": 7234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kennan Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please look for future announcements about partnership activities between the Wilson Center and the Kennan Institute at Wilson Center Press Room.\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7337, \"end\": 7350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilson Center\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\"}, {\"begin\": 7359, \"end\": 7375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kennan Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 7379, \"end\": 7392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilson Center\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woodrow_Wilson_International_Center_for_Scholars\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kennan Institute is the premier US center for advanced research on Eurasia and the oldest and largest regional program at the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars.\", \"from\": 7405, \"to\": 7584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7409, \"end\": 7425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kennan Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kennan_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 7441, \"end\": 7443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.8160690795838722, \"rank\": 0.2253603680536464, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7476, \"end\": 7483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Political_geography_of_Nineteen_Eighty-Four\", \"score\": 0.9987697447376316, \"rank\": 0.0012317706517539287, \"text\": \"Eurasia\", \"types\": [], \"wiki